==============================  CFJ 1566  ==============================

    Eris is guilty of Delay of Game after Quazie played Your Turn
    indicating Eris.

========================================================================

Caller:                                 Quazie
Barred:                                 Taral

Judge:                                  root
Judgement:                              FALSE

========================================================================

History:

Called by Quazie:                       13 May 2005 18:57:32 GMT
Assigned to root:                       15 May 2005 20:17:51 GMT
Judged FALSE by root:                   22 May 2005 18:54:35 GMT

========================================================================

Caller's Arguments:

Although R1016 states that an inactive player may not be required to
do something, i believe that Your Turn does not pose a requirement but
rather gives the indicated player an ultimatum.  They should do action
x and if they don't then result y happens.   Although the word must is
used in the Your Turn exploit, due to the fact that there is an or
clause, i believe that in reality it is not pose a requirement upon
the indicated player.

========================================================================

